Package com.iontrading.mkv

Class MkvPattern

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.iontrading.mkv.MkvObject
      • com.iontrading.mkv.MkvPattern
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    PrivateMkvPattern
    @Keep
@KeepPublicClassMemberNames
public class MkvPattern
extends MkvObject
    The MkvView class wraps a ION Pattern in a Java Object.

    A ION Pattern provides a facility for subscribing a great number of records with a common prefix at once.

    Unless otherwise noted, passing a null argument to a constructor or method in this class will cause a NullPointerException to be thrown.

      • subscribe

        public void subscribe​(String[] fields,
                      MkvRecordListener lner)
               throws MkvObjectNotAvailableException,
                      MkvTypeNotFoundException,
                      MkvConnectionException
        Subscribes the specified fields with the specified MkvRecordListener.

        Updates on the requested fields will be notified via the specified MkvRecordListener listener invocations.

        Parameters:
        fields - the fields to register.
        lner - the MkvRecordListener to register.
        Throws:
        MkvObjectNotAvailableException - if this MkvPattern is not available on the Platform.
        MkvTypeNotFoundException - if the type of this pattern is not available.
        MkvFieldNotFoundException - if a specified field is not part of this MkvPattern type.
        MkvConnectionException - if the connection with the publisher of this MkvPattern has been broken.
        See Also:
        MkvRecordListener
